The East Timor Parliament announced that it will use the [Portuguese
language](http://easttimorlegal.blogspot.com/2011/04/on-use-of-portuguese-in-
national.html?utm_source=feedburner&utm_medium=email&utm_campaign=Feed%3A+EastTimorLawJusticeBulletin+%28East+Timor+Law+&+Justice+Bulletin%29)
in plenary sessions at least once a month. A blogger reacts: “It would be like
the Australian or United States or English legislatures publishing new laws in
Japanese.”

